  "informal_statement": "The Jacobian Conjecture (Keller 1939) is FALSE in dimension 3: there is a polynomial map F : C^3 -> C^3 with a nonzero constant Jacobian determinant (a Keller map) that is not invertible. This packet certifies exactly the negated formal-conjectures instance jacobian_conjecture in dimension 3 - witness F(x,y,z) = ((1+xy)^3 z + y^2(1+xy)(4+3xy), y + 3x(1+xy)^2 z + 3xy^2(4+3xy), 2x - 3x^2 y - x^3 z), det Jac F = -2. It does NOT resolve the dimension-2 problem (open), the map's fiber/image geometry, general-n stabilization, or the Dixmier/Mathieu/Zhao/cubic-reduction bridges (open or only conditionally proved elsewhere).",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Instantiate the universally-quantified claim at the explicit Keller map F. Its Jacobian determinant is the nonzero constant -2 (kernel-checked: expand det via Matrix.det_fin_three, differentiate with pderiv, close with ring), so F satisfies the Keller hypothesis IsUnit (det Jac F). If F had a polynomial inverse G, evaluation composition would recover every point p from aeval p (F) via G; but F collapses the two distinct points (0,0,-1/4) and (1,-3/2,13/2) to the same image (-1/4,0,0) (kernel-checked by fin_cases + norm_num), so recovering the first coordinate forces 0 = 1, contradiction. Hence no such G exists and the instance is refuted.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem jacobian_conjecture_false_dim_three :\n    ¬ (∀ F : Fin 3 → MvPolynomial (Fin 3) ℂ,\n         IsUnit (Matrix.of fun i j => pderiv i (F j)).det →\n         ∃ G : Fin 3 → MvPolynomial (Fin 3) ℂ,\n           (fun i => bind₁ G (F i)) = X ∧ (fun i => bind₁ F (G i)) = X)",
